  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Use CloudKit Dashboard to verify existing record types, create new record types, edit fields, add search indexes, and delete record types that haven't been published to production."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To manage a schema’s record types, open CloudKit Dashboard, select your app’s container, and navigate to its Schema management page."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Inspect Record Types in CloudKit Dashboard",
          "anchor": "3403835"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If you create a record programmatically through just-in-time schema creation, use CloudKit Dashboard to verify that the record type appears in the schema with the name and fields you expect."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "From CloudKit Dashboard’s schema management page for your app’s container, verify that Record Types appears in the upper part of the left sidebar. Underneath, a list of system types and custom types appears."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "In the left sidebar, select a record type. The detail area on the right displays the field names and the field types for the record type you select. From here, you can add, modify, and remove undeployed fields and indexes."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-3699099",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "3699099",
                "title": "Figure 1"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For more information about just-in-time schema creation, see "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/cloudkit/designing_and_creating_a_cloudkit_database#3403832"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Enable Querying for Your Record Type in CloudKit Dashboard",
          "anchor": "3404860"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When designing and debugging your database, you might find it useful to search for records with a given record type. To enable searching for records by type, you must first add an index to a field on your record type."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When you create a record programmatically, iCloud creates a "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "recordName"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " metadata field in the corresponding record type. You add a "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "QUERYABLE"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " index to this field to enable searching for records by type in both CloudKit Dashboard and code."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To enable querying:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "From CloudKit Dashboard’s schema management page for your app’s container, verify that Record Types appears in the upper part of the left sidebar."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "In the right panel, at the bottom right of the Custom Fields section, click Edit Indexes. The subsection selector at the upper left changes to Indexes, and the record type’s indexes appear in the right panel."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "At the bottom of the right panel, click Add Index. Field name and index type selectors appear above."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "For the field, select "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "recordName"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ", and for the index type, select "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "QUERYABLE"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Click Save Changes. The "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "recordName"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " index appears in the right panel, and you can now search for records of that type."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-3699101",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "3699101",
                "title": "Figure 2"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Create a Record Type in CloudKit Dashboard",
          "anchor": "3404832"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In addition to creating record types programmatically using just-in-time schema creation, you can create new record types directly in CloudKit Dashboard."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "From CloudKit Dashboard’s schema management page for your app’s container, verify that Record Types appears in the upper part of the left sidebar."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "In the left sidebar, click the New Type button and provide a name for the new record type in the field that appears above."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "To add a field, click Add Field in the right panel, enter a field name, and select a field type from the menu."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "To delete a field, click the Delete button (-) in the row of the field in the right panel. The Delete button doesn’t function for fields that are in production."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Click Save. CloudKit adds the new record type to the schema."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-3699108",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "3699108",
                "title": "Figure 3"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Delete a Record Type in CloudKit Dashboard",
          "anchor": "3404831"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can delete a record type only in the development environment and only when that record type isn’t in production. Deleting a record type also deletes any corresponding records from the database."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "From CloudKit Dashboard’s schema management page for your app’s container, verify that Record Types appears in the upper part of the sidebar."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "In the left sidebar, select the record type you want to delete, and then click the Delete Type button. The Delete Type button doesn’t function for record types that are in production."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "In the dialog that appears, click Delete, and confirm that you want to delete the record type. CloudKit removes the record type and its corresponding records from the container."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-3699107",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "3699107",
                "title": "Figure 4"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        }
      ]
